  "prompt": "How is the word 'wretched' used in a sentence?",
  "response": "The word \"wretched\" is an adjective used to describe something or someone as extremely unfortunate, miserable, or of poor quality. Here are a few examples of how it can be used in a sentence:\n\n1. **Describing a person's condition**:  \n   - \"After days lost in the wilderness, he looked wretched and exhausted.\"  \n\n2. **Expressing pity or sympathy**:  \n   - \"The wretched child had nowhere to go after the storm destroyed his home.\"  \n\n3. **Describing something of poor quality**:  \n   - \"The hotel room was wretched, with dirty sheets and a broken air conditioner.\"  \n\n4. **Expressing frustration or annoyance**:  \n   - \"She was stuck in wretched traffic for hours on her way to the airport.\"  \n\nIn each case, \"wretched\" conveys a sense of extreme discomfort, unhappiness, or inferiority.",
